# The admin app ships as fixed-name bundles (/admin/assets/sponsors.js,
# sponsors.css) rather than content-hashed files. With normal caching a
# deploy can leave admins running a stale bundle for hours — which is
# exactly how a fixed client/server bug appeared "still broken" after it
# was deployed (the browser kept POSTing the old payload).
#
# Force these to always revalidate so a deploy is picked up on the next
# load. The admin HTML itself is tiny; keep it fresh too.
/admin/assets/sponsors.js
  Cache-Control: no-cache, must-revalidate
/admin/assets/sponsors.css
  Cache-Control: no-cache, must-revalidate
/admin/
  Cache-Control: no-cache, must-revalidate
/admin/index.html
  Cache-Control: no-cache, must-revalidate
